NEW ZEALANDERS L
Giving the next generation of achievers a boost
You're already taking great strides in your field, and your every
waking thought is about getting to the top in your sport. Now you
can achieve your goal with the help of a successful New Zealander
who has already done the hard graft.
Inspiring New Zealanders is a scholarship programme created by
a group of our most inspiring New Zealanders, with the help of
Air New Zealand and endorsed by the New Zealand Olympic
Committee. The scholarships will cover many disciplines, the first
of which is Olympic sports.
Up to eight scholarships are available for young athletes competing
in individual Olympic sports. Win one and you'll get the benefit of
one-on-one mentoring from Sarah Ulmer, Hamish Carter,
Bevan Docherty or Claudia Riegler. You'll also receive one return
economy class trip to an Air New Zealand destination to help you
compete overseas.
If you are already amongst the best of your age-group in New Zealand
but you haven't yet represented New Zealand at a Commonwealth
Games or an Olympic Games an Inspiring New Zealanders scholarship
could help you achieve it. So what's stopping you? Check out if you
are eligible and send in your application by 31 September 2005.
To find out how you can apply for a scholarship go online to
www.inspiringnewzealanders.com
